{%- comment -%}
  Marks a field inside a REPEATED record in stores.settings (programs[2].title,
  campaigns[0].description, impactStats[1].value …) as click-to-editable.

  Usage, inside a {% for %} with forloop available:
    <h3 {% render 'classic/snippets/editable-item',
          list: 'programs', index: forloop.index0, key: 'title', value: program.title %}>
      {{ program.title }}
    </h3>

  The list name and the index are BOTH required: without them an edit cannot say
  which record it belongs to, and the admin would have to guess — which is how you
  overwrite the wrong programme.

  Editing an existing record's text is all this covers. Adding, removing and
  reordering records stay in the drawer, because there is no text on the page to
  click for a record that does not exist yet.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- comment -%}
  Emits NOTHING outside the editor: these attributes carry the merchant's stored
  copy, and a visitor has no business receiving it.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if editing -%}data-mcloud-list="{{ list }}" data-mcloud-index="{{ index }}" data-mcloud-key="{{ key }}" data-mcloud-stored="{{ value | escape }}"{%- endif -%}
